Hitler's WebSiteby Ian Brown (1 level for the 2nd Encounter)Some StuffThis level is designed for use with the 2nd Encounter, and was made by Ian Brown. He is also the author of the following scenarios :Castle Hohenschastein and Siberian OffensiveAs of I know, he is one of the few active scenario creators of Mac Wolf. His scenarios are VERY solid and good, but his graphics creating ability is excellent! I so dearly hope everyone who plays this scenario or any other of his to send feedback to the author. Please remember, your mail could be the one to persuade and encourage the author to go on releasing new scenarios in the future!!CopyrightsJust give the author proper credit and keep everything intact. This is what the authors writes :Authors may use this level as a base to build additional levels, provided you inform me of your intentions.  You may distribute this SCENARIO, provided you include this file, with no modifications, along with any documentation. You may distribute this file in any electronic format (BBS, Diskette, CD, etc) as long as you include this file intact and send me a copy of the finished product as you plan to release it.Send comments to : ian.brown@sparticus.netDo anything at your own risk!!Well, hope you enjoy this!Webmaster of "the Wolfenstein Chronicle",Clubeyhttp://www1.linkclub.or.jp/~clubey/clubey@rg7.so-net.ne.jp------------------------------------------------------------------Appendix : Creator / File TypeTo play scenarios with the 1st and 2nd Encounter change the creator/type to:W3dE/W3dLTo play scenarios with Greg Ewing's splendid 4th Encounter (2nd Encounter installed) change creator/type to:W3E2/W3L2To play scenarios with the 3rd Encounter or the Commercial version change creator/type to:WOLF/MAPS